    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing is_cset0_present() function for MIB controlResourceSetZero validation\n\n### Summary\nThe UE MAC layer was missing the `is_cset0_present()` function that is needed to check if the controlResourceSetZero field is properly configured in the MIB. This caused issues when trying to validate PDCCH configuration during initial cell selection.\n\nThis fix implements the missing function in the NR MAC UE layer and adds the proper header declaration.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/mac_proto.h`: Added function declaration for `is_cset0_present()`\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Implemented `is_cset0_present()` function that checks if MIB controlResourceSetZero is present and valid\n\nWhen calling `is_cset0_present()` the behavior now correctly returns false when MIB is not initialized or when controlResourceSetZero has an invalid value (-1), and true when it has a valid value (>= 0).\n"
}